title: Game Theory and Money: Week 8 Predictions
itunes:title: Game Theory and Money: Week 8 Predictions
description:
"This just feels like an Aaron Rodgers game, right? Oh you're the new fangled offense? Oh you're the new kids, you think you're pretty special huh? Well let me show you what the greatest QB in the history of the game can do."

So do Cynthia Frelund's 10-thousand simulations of Packers-Rams agree? Go to the 37:20 mark and find out that along with the rest of the Week 8 predictions in this week's Game Theory and Money podcasts.

Redskins-Giants (3:57). Jets-Bears (6:54). Buccaneers-Bengals (10:10). Colts-Raiders (13:30). Dolphins-Texans (19:20). Ravens-Panthers (23:50). Jaguars-Eagles (28:10). Broncos-Chiefs (32:40). Packers-Rams (37:20). Patriots-Bills (39:30). HOW OFTEN DO TIES HAPPEN? (43:00). Browns-Steelers (43:55). Seahawks-Lions (47:05). FANTASY FUTIRES (52:00). 49ers-Cardinals (52:30). Saints-Vikings (53:30). CONFIDENCE PICKS (54:45)
